<TITLE> Vit A probe recommends against summer season campaign </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 15 (bdnews24.com)An investigation committee found no irregularities in the June 6 national drive to administer Vitamin-A capsules and de-worming tablets to 20 million children countrywide, but recommended against running such a drive during the summer season in future. Health minister AFM Ruhul Haque revealed the investigation committee's report before the press on Monday. "The investigation found children who were reported ill in the incident areas were already affected by diarrhoea and heat prior to taking the medicines," said the minister. "The committee cautions against holding future drives in the hot season." The health ministry formed the probe committee on Jun 8 to look into reports of hundreds of children falling ill after the drive. bd
